Reasoning: The paper deals with computer vision applications and robust estimation of camera motion and 3D structure, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of RANSAC and minimal solvers also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses polynomial solvers and basis selection, which are relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
